# UI & Styling Patterns

## Component Library
- Use Shadcn UI components as the foundation
- Built on Radix UI primitives for accessibility
- Customize components through CSS variables and Tailwind
- Maintain consistent design system across the application

## Tailwind CSS Usage
- Use utility-first approach for styling
- Leverage Tailwind's design tokens for consistency
- Use responsive design patterns with mobile-first approach
- Implement dark/light mode support

## Component Structure
- Create reusable UI components in `src/components/ui/`
- Use compound component patterns for complex UI elements
- Implement proper prop interfaces with TypeScript
- Follow accessibility best practices (ARIA labels, keyboard navigation)

## Styling Best Practices
- Use CSS variables for theme customization
- Implement consistent spacing and typography scales
- Use Lucide icons for consistent iconography
- Optimize for performance with CSS-in-JS considerations

## Responsive Design
- Mobile-first responsive design approach
- Use Tailwind's responsive prefixes consistently
- Test across different screen sizes and devices
- Implement proper touch targets for mobile interfaces